{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"I'm a neuroscientist,"},{"time":2040,"text":"and I'm the co-founder of Backyard Brains,"},{"time":4360,"text":"and our mission is to train\nthe next generation of neuroscientists"},{"time":8240,"text":"by taking graduate-level\nneuroscience research equipment"},{"time":11280,"text":"and making it available for kids\nin middle schools and high schools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15520,"text":"And so when we go into the classroom,"},{"time":17400,"text":"one way to get them thinking\nabout the brain, which is very complex,"},{"time":21320,"text":"is to ask them a very simple\nquestion about neuroscience,"},{"time":24280,"text":"and that is, \"What has a brain?\""},{"time":27040,"text":"When we ask that,"},{"time":28320,"text":"students will instantly tell you\nthat their cat or dog has a brain,"},{"time":32400,"text":"and most will say that a mouse\nor even a small insect has a brain,"},{"time":37000,"text":"but almost nobody says\nthat a plant or a tree"},{"time":39840,"text":"or a shrub has a brain."},{"time":42040,"text":"And so when you push --"},{"time":44560,"text":"because this could actually\nhelp describe a little bit"},{"time":47160,"text":"how the brain actually functions --"},{"time":49360,"text":"so you push and say,"},{"time":50600,"text":"\"Well, what is it that makes\nliving things have brains versus not?\""},{"time":54160,"text":"And often they'll come back\nwith the classification"},{"time":56640,"text":"that things that move tend to have brains."},{"time":60440,"text":"And that's absolutely correct."},{"time":62080,"text":"Our nervous system evolved\nbecause it is electrical."},{"time":64560,"text":"It's fast, so we can quickly respond\nto stimuli in the world"},{"time":67720,"text":"and move if we need to."},{"time":69960,"text":"But you can go back\nand push back on a student,"},{"time":72200,"text":"and say, \"Well, you know,\nyou say that plants don't have brains,"},{"time":75280,"text":"but plants do move.\""},{"time":76760,"text":"Anyone who has grown a plant"},{"time":78640,"text":"has noticed that the plant will move"},{"time":80640,"text":"and face the sun."},{"time":82480,"text":"But they'll say,\n\"But that's a slow movement."},{"time":84640,"text":"You know, that doesn't count.\nThat could be a chemical process.\""},{"time":87680,"text":"But what about fast-moving plants?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90080,"text":"Now, in 1760, Arthur Dobbs,\nthe Royal Governor of North Carolina,"},{"time":95200,"text":"made a pretty fascinating discovery."},{"time":97760,"text":"In the swamps behind his house,"},{"time":100640,"text":"he found a plant that would spring shut"},{"time":104320,"text":"every time a bug would fall in between it."},{"time":107720,"text":"He called this plant the flytrap,"},{"time":110680,"text":"and within a decade,\nit made its way over to Europe,"},{"time":113640,"text":"where eventually the great Charles Darwin\ngot to study this plant,"},{"time":117200,"text":"and this plant absolutely blew him away."},{"time":119240,"text":"He called it the most wonderful\nplant in the world."},{"time":121800,"text":"This is a plant\nthat was an evolutionary wonder."},{"time":124080,"text":"This is a plant that moves quickly,"},{"time":126080,"text":"which is rare,"},{"time":127400,"text":"and it's carnivorous, which is also rare."},{"time":129400,"text":"And this is in the same plant."},{"time":130880,"text":"But I'm here today to tell you"},{"time":132360,"text":"that's not even the coolest thing\nabout this plant."},{"time":134800,"text":"The coolest thing\nis that the plant can count."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138560,"text":"So in order to show that,"},{"time":139960,"text":"we have to get some vocabulary\nout of the way."},{"time":142160,"text":"So I'm going to do what we do\nin the classroom with students."},{"time":145440,"text":"We're going to do\nan experiment on electrophysiology,"},{"time":149320,"text":"which is the recording\nof the body's electrical signal,"},{"time":152480,"text":"either coming from neurons\nor from muscles."},{"time":154800,"text":"And I'm putting some electrodes\nhere on my wrists."},{"time":157160,"text":"As I hook them up,"},{"time":158520,"text":"we're going to be able to see a signal"},{"time":160720,"text":"on the screen here."},{"time":162200,"text":"And this signal may be familiar to you."},{"time":164120,"text":"It's called the EKG,\nor the electrocardiogram."},{"time":166320,"text":"And this is coming\nfrom neurons in my heart"},{"time":168800,"text":"that are firing\nwhat's called action potentials,"},{"time":171360,"text":"potential meaning voltage and action\nmeaning it moves quickly up and down,"},{"time":175240,"text":"which causes my heart to fire,"},{"time":176720,"text":"which then causes\nthe signal that you see here."},{"time":179560,"text":"And so I want you to remember the shape\nof what we'll be looking at right here,"},{"time":183320,"text":"because this is going to be important."},{"time":185200,"text":"This is a way that the brain\nencodes information"},{"time":187640,"text":"in the form of an action potential."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189360,"text":"So now let's turn to some plants."},{"time":192920,"text":"So I'm going to first\nintroduce you to the mimosa,"},{"time":196480,"text":"not the drink, but the Mimosa pudica,"},{"time":199720,"text":"and this is a plant that's found\nin Central America and South America,"},{"time":203080,"text":"and it has behaviors."},{"time":205080,"text":"And the first behavior\nI'm going to show you"},{"time":207200,"text":"is if I touch the leaves here,"},{"time":209320,"text":"you get to see that the leaves\ntend to curl up."},{"time":213280,"text":"And then the second behavior is,"},{"time":215560,"text":"if I tap the leaf,"},{"time":217760,"text":"the entire branch seems to fall down."},{"time":219600,"text":"So why does it do that?"},{"time":221160,"text":"It's not really known to science."},{"time":222800,"text":"One of the reasons why\ncould be that it scares away insects"},{"time":226040,"text":"or it looks less appealing to herbivores."},{"time":228240,"text":"But how does it do that?\nNow, that's interesting."},{"time":230760,"text":"We can do an experiment to find out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232920,"text":"So what we're going to do now,"},{"time":234400,"text":"just like I recorded\nthe electrical potential from my body,"},{"time":237840,"text":"we're going to record the electrical\npotential from this plant, this mimosa."},{"time":241680,"text":"And so what we're going to do\nis I've got a wire wrapped around the stem,"},{"time":247200,"text":"and I've got the ground electrode where?"},{"time":250360,"text":"In the ground. It's an electrical\nengineering joke. Alright."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":254680,"text":"Alright. So I'm going to go ahead\nand tap the leaf here,"},{"time":257440,"text":"and I want you to look\nat the electrical recording"},{"time":259839,"text":"that we're going to see inside the plant."},{"time":262520,"text":"Whoa. It is so big,\nI've got to scale it down."},{"time":265440,"text":"Alright. So what is that?"},{"time":266880,"text":"That is an action potential\nthat is happening inside the plant."},{"time":269880,"text":"Why was it happening?"},{"time":271160,"text":"Because it wanted to move. Right?"},{"time":272800,"text":"And so when I hit the touch receptors,"},{"time":275840,"text":"it sent a voltage all the way down\nto the end of the stem,"},{"time":279040,"text":"which caused it to move."},{"time":280320,"text":"And now, in our arms,\nwe would move our muscles,"},{"time":282600,"text":"but the plant doesn't have muscles."},{"time":284320,"text":"What it has is water inside the cells"},{"time":286600,"text":"and when the voltage hits it,\nit opens up, releases the water,"},{"time":289560,"text":"changes the shape of the cells,\nand the leaf falls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292480,"text":"OK. So here we see an action potential\nencoding information to move. Alright?"},{"time":297440,"text":"But can it do more?"},{"time":298960,"text":"So let's go to find out."},{"time":300240,"text":"We're going to go to our good friend,\nthe Venus flytrap here,"},{"time":303320,"text":"and we're going to take a look\nat what happens inside the leaf"},{"time":307760,"text":"when a fly lands on here."},{"time":309720,"text":"So I'm going to pretend\nto be a fly right now."},{"time":312440,"text":"And now here's my Venus flytrap,"},{"time":314120,"text":"and inside the leaf,\nyou're going to notice"},{"time":316160,"text":"that there are three little hairs here,\nand those are trigger hairs."},{"time":319400,"text":"And so when a fly lands --"},{"time":320800,"text":"I'm going to touch\none of the hairs right now."},{"time":323320,"text":"Ready? One, two, three."},{"time":327000,"text":"What do we get? We get\na beautiful action potential."},{"time":329480,"text":"However, the flytrap doesn't close."},{"time":332640,"text":"And to understand why that is,"},{"time":334120,"text":"we need to know a little bit more\nabout the behavior of the flytrap."},{"time":337360,"text":"Number one is that it takes\na long time to open the traps back up --"},{"time":340680,"text":"you know, about 24 to 48 hours\nif there's no fly inside of it."},{"time":344880,"text":"And so it takes a lot of energy."},{"time":346600,"text":"And two, it doesn't need to eat\nthat many flies throughout the year."},{"time":349840,"text":"Only a handful. It gets\nmost of its energy from the sun."},{"time":352520,"text":"It's just trying to replace\nsome nutrients in the ground with flies."},{"time":355760,"text":"And the third thing is,"},{"time":357040,"text":"it only opens then closes the traps\na handful of times"},{"time":360040,"text":"until that trap dies."},{"time":362120,"text":"So therefore, it wants\nto make really darn sure"},{"time":364840,"text":"that there's a meal inside of it\nbefore the flytrap snaps shut."},{"time":369280,"text":"So how does it do that?"},{"time":371280,"text":"It counts the number of seconds"},{"time":373920,"text":"between successive\ntouching of those hairs."},{"time":377160,"text":"And so the idea is\nthat there's a high probability,"},{"time":379600,"text":"if there's a fly inside of there,\nthey're going to be quick together,"},{"time":383080,"text":"and so when it gets the first\naction potential,"},{"time":385320,"text":"it starts counting, one, two,"},{"time":386760,"text":"and if it gets to 20\nand it doesn't fire again,"},{"time":389000,"text":"then it's not going to close,"},{"time":390440,"text":"but if it does it within there,\nthen the flytrap will close."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393320,"text":"So we're going to go back now."},{"time":394800,"text":"I'm going to touch\nthe Venus flytrap again."},{"time":396840,"text":"I've been talking\nfor more than 20 seconds."},{"time":398880,"text":"So we can see what happens\nwhen I touch the hair a second time."},{"time":403720,"text":"So what do we get?\nWe get a second action potential,"},{"time":406200,"text":"but again, the leaf doesn't close."},{"time":408120,"text":"So now if I go back in there"},{"time":410080,"text":"and if I'm a fly moving around,"},{"time":412000,"text":"I'm going to be touching\nthe leaf a few times."},{"time":414200,"text":"I'm going to go and brush it a few times."},{"time":416640,"text":"And immediately,"},{"time":418080,"text":"the flytrap closes."},{"time":419840,"text":"So here we are seeing the flytrap\nactually doing a computation."},{"time":424000,"text":"It's determining\nif there's a fly inside the trap,"},{"time":426520,"text":"and then it closes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428040,"text":"So let's go back to our original question."},{"time":431520,"text":"Do plants have brains?"},{"time":433840,"text":"Well, the answer is no."},{"time":435440,"text":"There's no brains in here."},{"time":436840,"text":"There's no axons, no neurons."},{"time":440440,"text":"It doesn't get depressed."},{"time":441840,"text":"It doesn't want to know\nwhat the Tigers' score is."},{"time":444240,"text":"It doesn't have\nself-actualization problems."},{"time":446360,"text":"But what it does have\nis something that's very similar to us,"},{"time":449800,"text":"which is the ability\nto communicate using electricity."},{"time":452880,"text":"It just uses slightly\ndifferent ions than we do,"},{"time":455160,"text":"but it's actually doing the same thing."},{"time":457200,"text":"So just to show you"},{"time":459400,"text":"the ubiquitous nature\nof these action potentials,"},{"time":462720,"text":"we saw it in the Venus flytrap,"},{"time":464960,"text":"we've seen an action\npotential in the mimosa."},{"time":467120,"text":"We've even seen\nan action potential in a human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469520,"text":"Now, this is the euro of the brain."},{"time":472760,"text":"It's the way that all\ninformation is passed."},{"time":474920,"text":"And so what we can do\nis we can use those action potentials"},{"time":477760,"text":"to pass information"},{"time":479280,"text":"between species of plants."},{"time":481040,"text":"And so this is our interspecies\nplant-to-plant communicator,"},{"time":485480,"text":"and what we've done\nis we've created a brand new experiment"},{"time":488680,"text":"where we're going to record\nthe action potential from a Venus flytrap,"},{"time":492240,"text":"and we're going to send it\ninto the sensitive mimosa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495040,"text":"So I want you to recall what happens"},{"time":496800,"text":"when we touch the leaves of the mimosa."},{"time":498760,"text":"It has touch receptors\nthat are sending that information"},{"time":501440,"text":"back down in the form\nof an action potential."},{"time":503560,"text":"And so what would happen"},{"time":504920,"text":"if we took the action potential\nfrom the Venus flytrap"},{"time":508560,"text":"and sent it into\nall the stems of the mimosa?"},{"time":512440,"text":"We should be able to create\nthe behavior of the mimosas"},{"time":515480,"text":"without actually touching it ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517400,"text":"And so if you'll allow me,"},{"time":519440,"text":"I'm going to go ahead\nand trigger this mimosa right now"},{"time":522919,"text":"by touching on the hairs\nof the Venus flytrap."},{"time":526760,"text":"So we're going to send information\nabout touch from one plant to another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534640,"text":"So there you see it."},{"time":536360,"text":"So --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":537600,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":543640,"text":"So I hope you learned a little bit,\nsomething about plants today,"},{"time":546720,"text":"and not only that."},{"time":547960,"text":"You learned that plants could be used\nto help teach neuroscience"},{"time":551000,"text":"and bring along the neurorevolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552760,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}